org.paces.Stata.Input.Interfaces

Interface RowValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    StataVariableCreator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RowValueImpl

    public interface RowValue
extends StataVariableCreator
    Interface used to load JSON values into separate variables in the DataSet. Essentially it takes the Flattened JSON object and transforms the n x 2 Matrix into a single row vector.
    Version:
    0.0.0
    Author:
    Billy Buchanan

        Parameters:

        nodeMap - The Flattened JSON Object

      • loadLong

        default void loadLong(java.lang.Integer obid,
                      java.lang.Integer varidx,
                      FlatStataJSON datum,
                      java.lang.String key)
        Method used to load Java ints (Stata longs). 4-bit Integers are labelled "long" in Stata notation, so the method reflects what would be consumed by end users working in Stata.
        Parameters:
        obid - The observation ID where the datum will be stored
        varidx - The variable index where the variable will be stored
        datum - A FlatStataJSON object containing the JsonNode object
        key - The key to the JsonNode object (also the variable label)

      • loadDouble

        default void loadDouble(java.lang.Integer obid,
                        java.lang.Integer varidx,
                        FlatStataJSON datum,
                        java.lang.String key)
        Method used to load floating point and 64-bit Integer numeric values into Stata. Java long types require 64-bits, but the maximum integer length currently available in Stata is 32-bit; these values are cast up to a double via the underlying Number interface.
        Parameters:
        obid - The observation ID where the datum will be stored
        varidx - The variable index where the variable will be stored
        datum - A FlatStataJSON object containing the JsonNode object
        key - The key to the JsonNode object (also the variable label)
